LESSION 4 - Servlet and JSP.

* there are 2 types of request from browser.

        1) Static request   - it means the data is static for all. like login page, any news website. any tutorials website. because it has static data for all.
        2) Dynamic request  - it means, we request the specific data. search for specific data. we search specific video in youtube.

* when we are hitting dynamic request, it will be reached by web container which resides inside server. which name is web container.
* web container is the one where all servlets resides.


        Q) what is servlet ?

            * simply, servlets is just a java file.
            * this java file runs on server side, might have a name as servlet.



* we are doing multiple dynamic request right, in web container there are multiple servlets right.
* so how do we know which servlets will map to which request and how the response will be delivered.


        Q) how requests are catched and processed ?

            * there is a file named web.xml which has the details of servlet mappings.
            * it has the details of which is request is mapped to which servlet.


* web.xml also called as 'Deployment Descriptor'.


